CSS basics

- selectors: can be HTML elements, classes (use a dot)
- properties: colors, fonts (size, family), background (color, images)
- box style: introduce divs 
- 


HTML element {
	property: value;
}

.class {
	property: value;
}

#id {
	property:value;
}

- color property:
  text color
  RGB values (0-255)
  hex numbers (00-ff)

- font-size
  pixels vs. ems vs. rems

